summary: Census Designated is the second album by American producer and singer-songwriter Jane Remover, released via deadAir records on October 20th, 2023. The album was preceded by the release of its lead single, "Lips", on August 23, 2023, and was announced on the same day. Initial ideas for Census Designated were written and recorded just weeks after Frailty’s release, but took 18 months to perfect. During their first trip across America, Jane collected ambience and experience that texturized the embryo of Census Designated. summary: Frailty is the debut album by American producer and singer-songwriter Jane Remover, released via deadAir records on November 12, 2021, just 8 months after her EP, Teen Week. summary: I Love My Computer is the debut album from Australian electronic producer Ninajirachi, released on August 8, 2025.
